definitions.definition: A garment that is wrapped around the body and tied.
A label or advertising display that wraps around a container .
A segment where material featuring one person (such as a reporter ) is introduced and concluded by another person.
An extension to a property that combines side and rear additions.
Word wrap , the word processing feature that moves text to the beginning of the next line if it will not fit at the end of the current line.
The wrapping of numerical values in case of underflow or overflow .
examples: The addition of integers is unchecked, so wraparound occurs if the resulting value is beyond the representable range.

definitions.definition: An attempt to score by reaching around the side of the net from behind .

main_definition: ( countable ) A garment that is wrapped around the body and tied.
secondary_definitions: ( countable ) A label or advertising display that wraps around a container .
( countable , television , radio ) A segment where material featuring one person (such as a reporter ) is introduced and concluded by another person.
( countable , often attributive ) An extension to a property that combines side and rear additions.
( uncountable , countable , computing ) Word wrap , the word processing feature that moves text to the beginning of the next line if it will not fit at the end of the current line.
( uncountable , countable , programming ) The wrapping of numerical values in case of underflow or overflow .
( countable , ice hockey ) An attempt to score by reaching around the side of the net from behind .
